// Allow the ghostcam camera daemon (unprivileged `ghostcam` system user,
// member of `netdev`) to read the modem's location from ModemManager
// unattended. `mmcli -m 0 --location-get` is polkit-gated under the
// `org.freedesktop.ModemManager1.Location` action, which bookworm ships
// as `auth_admin_keep` — so a GUI-less daemon call fails with
// "PolicyKit authorization failed: not authorized", and the coarse
// cell-tower geolocation fallback (server resolves the reported
// MCC/MNC/LAC/CID to an approximate lat/lon when there's no GPS fix)
// never gets any cell data to report.
//
// Scoped to the `Location` action ONLY — deliberately NOT the blanket
// `org.freedesktop.ModemManager1.*` the way 49-ghostcam-nm.rules grants
// NetworkManager. ModemManager also gates Messaging (send SMS), Voice
// (place calls), and Contacts under separate actions; a camera has no
// business doing those, and on a metered/roaming SIM an errant SMS costs
// real money. The Location action covers both reading location and
// enabling location sources, which is all the daemon needs.
//
// Scoped to the netdev group (not the `ghostcam` user by name) so it
// composes with operator-added admin accounts, matching the NM rule.
// polkit reads rules at reload; the .deb postinst runs
// `systemctl reload polkit` after dropping it in place.
polkit.addRule(function (action, subject) {
    if (
        action.id.indexOf("org.freedesktop.ModemManager1.Location") === 0 &&
        subject.isInGroup("netdev")
    ) {
        return polkit.Result.YES;
    }
});
